Introduction

Weki Meki was an eight-member girl group under Fantagio. They debuted on August 8, 2017, with their first mini album, "WEME." On June 7, 2024, Fantagio announced that the group would disband on June 12 after releasing their final single, "CoinciDestiny."

Their fandom name, "Ki-Ling," is derived from the "Ki" in Weki Meki and "Ling" from the word "Darling." It also symbolizes a key ring, representing that Weki Meki is always with their fans.

The group's name stands for "eight unique girls (MeKi) that hold keys to know one another, and the girls together hold keys that open to another world (WeKi)."
